channel.title: RS Demon is profitable if used correctly?
channel.description:
http://www.pythonabc.php0h.com/readme.htm
RS Demon is a popular bot-application used to cut yew logs, the level three accounts you see around will properly be using this bot or something like this. It starts from level 1-60 then sticks to yews. A week key costs $2 or 600k.
These bots are known to hardly get banned, but you'll notice, it's the big "Bosses" who don't get caught and lose their money.
Starting with a account at 60 woodcutting, within four hours, depending on the axe type, you can easierly cut 2,000 yew logs. Which is around 600 - 640k.
If you where to wait untill you got to 2,000 yews, then transfer the money into a "Safe account". Then 10k yew logs later, the account was banned, you'd be able to re-register another week with the money you made off with.
Using RS demon is profitable when you know what you are doing. I'd like to know if anybody would like to comment on this idea and also if this would work?
Thanks.
